640
00:57:30,456 --> 00:57:33,057
When you run a household, you've got income, you've got expenses.

641
00:57:33,397 --> 00:57:41,640
If you make your operating budget, your normal budget for the year, you want to look at your income and hope that your budget adds up to less than your total income.

642
00:57:42,520 --> 00:57:45,921
And in your household, you probably also have a savings account.

643
00:57:46,850 --> 00:57:50,673
It's good to have a savings account for one time or unexpected expenses.

644
00:57:51,113 --> 00:57:55,136
Your kid might need braces, your roof might need repair, you might need to get a new car.

645
00:57:55,916 --> 00:57:58,458
Cities also need to have savings accounts for similar reasons.

646
00:57:58,925 --> 00:58:07,292
At some point, we will need a new fire station, we'll need a new high school, there might be a pandemic and our schools suddenly need HVAC systems to all be replaced at the same time.

647
00:58:07,873 --> 00:58:17,921
