651
00:58:29,032 --> 00:58:32,794
Every year, the city makes a budget and then throughout the year, we spend money.

652
00:58:33,314 --> 00:58:37,336
If we spend less than we budgeted, that amount left over is called free cash.

653
00:58:38,416 --> 00:58:40,837
So if we budget $180 million and then we spend $172 million, that gives us $8 million in free cash.

654
00:58:45,439 --> 00:58:51,761
And what's important to understand is that every city is strongly encouraged by the state to have free cash every year.

655
00:58:52,021 --> 00:58:54,121
Cities must spend less than their budget.

656
00:58:54,581 --> 00:58:57,122
If they spend more than their budget, their bond rating goes down.

657
00:58:57,422 --> 00:58:57,862
Bond rating.

658
00:58:58,002 --> 00:58:58,762
It's like a credit rating.

659
00:58:59,203 --> 00:59:03,444
And if your bond rating goes down, then it costs you an arm and a leg in interest and fees to borrow money.

660
00:59:04,784 --> 00:59:06,764
Spending more than you budgeted is a big no-no.

661
00:59:06,784 --> 00:59:08,765
It's a sign that your city is being poorly run.

662
00:59:09,597 --> 00:59:12,440
So yay for Medford that recently we have free cash every year.

663
00:59:12,681 --> 00:59:16,825
